.TH TFCTL-ATTRS 7 "2025-09-25" "tfctl" "Miscellaneous Information"
.SH NAME
tfctl-attrs \- attribute selection and transformation with tfctl
.SH SYNOPSIS
Use the
.BR \-\-attrs
flag with most commands to select and transform fields.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B \-\-attrs
flag accepts a comma\-separated list of extraction specs with optional renaming
and transformation directives.
.P
Each spec has the form:
.P
.RS
json_path:output_name:transform_spec
.RE
.P
See the project documentation for a complete guide to JSON paths, renaming, and
transformations.
.SH TRANSFORMS
.TP
.B U / L
Uppercase or lowercase.
.TP
.B N
Truncate to first N characters (e.g., "10"). Use negative N to compress the
middle (e.g., "-8").
.TP
.B t
Convert UTC timestamps to local time (uses the
.B TZ
environment variable when set).
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
# Select specific attributes
tfctl oq --attrs name,email,created-at

# Root\-level attributes
tfctl oq --attrs .id,.type

# Rename outputs
tfctl oq --attrs created-at:Created,email:Admin

# Transformations
tfctl oq --attrs name::U,created-at::t,email::L10
.fi
